All studies will be obtained through a comprehensive search strategy using electronic and manual search methods to locate both indexed and non-indexed articles. Furthermore, hand-searching of reference lists of the reviewed articles were also examined. The electronic search strategy included the following databases: PubMed, Wiley, ScienceDirect, SCOPUS, and the Cochrane Central Register of Controlled Trials. No limitations of the date of publication and language were applied, and all records up to January 2020 were included using the following keywords respectively under the guidance of a librarian:

1.	dent* AND (student OR assess* OR evaluation) AND clinical AND (“technology-enhanced” OR virtual OR haptic);
2.	"dental student" AND (assess* OR evaluation) AND clinical AND (“technology-enhanced” OR virtual OR haptic OR simulation);
3.	(dental OR dentist) AND (student OR undergraduate) AND clinical AND ("technology enhanced" OR haptic) AND (assessment OR competency);
4.	dent* AND (student OR undergraduate) AND clinical AND ("technology-enhanced" OR haptic OR simul* OR virtual) AND (assess* OR competency);
5.	dent* AND (student OR undergraduate) AND clinical AND ("technology-enhanced" OR haptic OR digital OR 3D OR simul* OR virtual OR computer OR e-learning).

The manual hand-search included the following four journals:

1.	Journal of  Dental Education (2000-2019);
2.	European Journal of Dental Education (2000-2019);
3.	International Journal of Technology Assessment in Healthcare (2001-2019);
4.	Medical Teacher (2000-2019).

